# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# graphify corpus scope — Abelard.  CODE-ONLY.
#
# Doctrine, docs, configs, secrets, virtualenvs, caches and fixtures are EXCLUDED.
#
# WHY code-only is the whole game here: graphify only invokes an LLM backend for
# document/paper/image files (.md/.txt/.rst/.html/.yaml/.yml/.pdf/images/office/
# video). A pure-code corpus never enters that path, so extraction is 100% local
# AST (tree-sitter) — zero network calls, zero API cost. Excluding every doc-class
# file is therefore BOTH the doctrine safeguard AND the offline guarantee.
#
# graphify merges .gitignore + .graphifyignore (gitignore semantics: last-match-
# wins, '!' negation, parent-exclusion). A '!' here can NEVER re-include a file
# that .gitignore already excludes (.venv/, .env, *.env, __pycache__/, *.db,
# *.egg-info/, .pytest_cache/, build/, dist/) — an extra safety floor under the
# allowlist below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Exclude everything, then re-include ONLY the source trees.
#    (daemons/common/abelard_common/ lives under daemons/, so it is covered.)
*
!daemons/
!daemons/**
!scripts/
!scripts/**

# 2) Doctrine — must never enter the corpus. Redundant with *.md below, but
#    listed explicitly so the intent is auditable. Bare names match at any depth,
#    so the per-daemon SOUL.md files are caught too.
SOUL.md
IDENTITY.md
USER.md
AGENTS.md
SECURITY.md
WORLDVIEW.md
THESES.md
METHODOLOGY.md
MEMORY.md

# 3) ALL doc / prose / config / media extensions — keeps the corpus code-only,
#    which is what keeps extraction fully offline (see header).
*.md
*.markdown
*.mdx
*.qmd
*.rst
*.txt
*.html
*.htm
*.yaml
*.yml
*.pdf
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.webp
*.svg
*.docx
*.xlsx
*.mp4
*.mov
*.webm
*.mkv
*.avi
*.m4v
*.mp3
*.wav
*.m4a
*.ogg
*.gdoc
*.gsheet
*.gslides

# 4) Secrets / virtualenvs / caches / build artifacts. Most are already in
#    .gitignore, but .venv-linux/ is NOT, so cover the venv variants explicitly.
.env
*.env
.venv/
.venv*/
venv/
**/__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite3

# 5) Test fixtures (captured payloads / data, not source).
**/tests/fixtures/**

# 6) graphify's own output directory.
graphify-out/
